message.content: "If it is-" she laughed uncertainly - "you can have your ring back." She loosened the heavy heap of diamonds on her left hand third finger and held it out to him, still playfully. Without a glimmer of amusement in his own eyes, however, he took it, looking moodily beyond her. "Perhaps it's as well if you can't wear it for a bit, Di," he told her.
